main event: An unidentified rock-like object was found in a field near Frenchman's Bayou, Arkansas, on 21 May 1958, and was determined to be possibly a stone of some sort.
interesting points: The object was not usually found in the area and was turned over to the station representative by the field owner.
The image includes a photographic print of the rock or stone formation, providing a visual of the unidentified object.
The request for evaluation of the object was addressed to the Air Technical Intelligence Center at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base, Ohio.
The document references further recovery efforts and analysis of the item by the ATIC in case additional findings arise.
The preliminary analysis of the object concluded it to be of meteoric origin, with further recovery efforts and analysis planned.
